        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ui): per-agent ElevenLabs Voice/TTS settings in control-ui",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw supports per-agent TTS configuration via `agents.list[].tts` in the config schema, but there is no UI to set it — users had to manually edit YAML/JSON. This PR adds a Voice/TTS settings card to the agent overview panel in the control-ui, so per-agent ElevenLabs voice configuration (enable toggle, provider, API key, voice ID, model) can be set directly from the UI.\n\n## Summary\n\nAdds a Voice/TTS settings card to the agent overview panel in the control-ui, allowing per-agent ElevenLabs configuration (API key, voice ID, model) directly from the UI.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`agents-panels-overview.ts`**: New `AgentTtsConfig` type, `resolveAgentTts()` helper, and Voice/TTS card section with enable toggle, provider dropdown, ElevenLabs API key (password field), Voice ID, and Model Selector\n- **`agents.ts`**: 5 new TTS handler props wired through to overview\n- **`app-render.ts`**: TTS handlers (`onTtsToggle`, `onTtsProviderChange`, `onTtsApiKeyChange`, `onTtsVoiceIdChange`, `onTtsModelChange`) using existing `updateConfigFormValue` + `ensureAgentIndex` pattern\n- **`en.ts` + 18 non-English locales**: i18n strings for voice/TTS section\n- **`components.css`**: Toggle-switch CSS\n- **`agents.test.ts`**: Mock handlers for new TTS props + regression test for conditional ElevenLabs fields rendering\n\n## Config path\n\nWrites to `agents.list[].tts` with `enabled`, `provider`, `providers.elevenlabs.{apiKey, speakerVoiceId, model}` — all pre-existing OpenClaw config schema fields.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Build**: `pnpm build` passes clean\n- **Tests**: 2299 passed, 31 skipped (only pre-existing flaky failures unrelated to changes)\n- **i18n alignment**: 11/11 locale structural tests pass\n- **Regression test**: \"renders ElevenLabs fields when provider is elevenlabs\" — passes (5ms)\n- **Local deployment**: Built and deployed to `~/.local/npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/control-ui/`. Voice/TTS card renders correctly in agents overview tab with enable toggle, provider dropdown, and conditional ElevenLabs fields (API key, Voice ID, Model) appearing when \"ElevenLabs\" is selected.\n- **Reactivity fix**: Initial deployment had a bug where conditional fields did not render (undefined `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` variable reference threw at render time). Fixed in commit `e39402bc9f` — fields now render correctly on provider selection.\n\n## Files changed\n\n42 files, +881/-72 lines (7 commits)",
